## Day 1: Setting Up Development Environment

### Required Software
1. Code Editor/IDE Options:
   - Visual Studio Code
  

### Setting Up VS Code for C++
1. Install VS Code
2. Install Required Extensions:
   - C/C++ extension by Microsoft
   - Code Runner (optional)
3. Install C++ Compiler (MinGW for Windows):
   - Download MinGW installer
   - Select and install gcc and g++ packages
   - Add compiler to system PATH

